comment.en: The pascal is the SI derived unit of pressure used to quantify internal pressure, stress. It is defined as one newton per square metre.

Volume is the quantity of three-dimensional space enclosed by a closed surface, for example, the space that a substance (solid, liquid, gas, or plasma) or shape occupies or contains. Volume is often quantified numerically using the cubic metre (m3).

A Location must have either a spatial relation to another location (e.g. "contained in"), a geographical coordinate representing its centre, or a pair of geographical coordintes representing it's outer boundaries (northwest/southeast)


An instance of Location can have a PopularName and isLocatedAt a geographical point.

E.g. Defining Stockholm as a Location:
LocationUUID#1 isA Location
LocationUUID#1 hasPopularName "Stockholm"
LocationUUID#1 isLocatedAt (59.333683,18.068579,0)
LocationUUID#1 isLocatedIn LocationUUID#2
An object that has an exact point (expressed in WGS84 in decimal degrees as (latitude,longitude,altitude).
Human-readable-friendly name.

For example an airtreatment device (Device) that serves several rooms (BuildingStructureComponent) or a full building (BuildingStructure). Can also be a Device (e.g. airtreatment device) serving another Device (e.g. air diffuser).

An object that can describe its place by using [object-UUID] locatedIn
[myOtherObject-UUID], where [myOtherObject-UUID] could be a Room, BuildingStructure, etc.
A Device serving another Device. E.g. an HVAC-unit serving an air diffuser.

Use this property to add [proprietary] regions.

The angle between one of the axis of a local coordinate system within e.g. a building and a north-south meridian. The angle is measured between the meridian and the local coordinate axis and counted as positive to the east side of the meridan (neagtive to the west side).

Bearings are never greater than 90°.
Bearings are based on true north.
Designation or enumeration commenly found on blueprints for an object. E.g. text designating a Device or a Room.
